Questions:
Find the tangent plane to the surface x=u+v, y=u²+v², z=u³+v³ at an arbitrary point:
(a) by taking the equation of the surface in the parametric form;
(b) by writing the equation of the surface in the form z=f(x,y).

Use the relationship proved in the previous problem for finding the gradient of the function:
(1) f=r²; (2) f=|r|; (3) f=F(r²); (4) f=(ar)(br); (5) f=(abr);
where a and b are constant vectors.
